  "prompt": "What does \"AAA\" mean in AAA title game?",
  "response": "In the context of video games, \"AAA\" (pronounced \"Triple A\") refers to titles that are produced by large, well-funded development teams and publishers, typically with high budgets and extensive marketing campaigns. These games are characterized by high production values, including advanced graphics, polished gameplay, in-depth narratives, and robust audio design. They are also often expected to deliver a significant return on investment and are usually aimed at mainstream markets. Examples of AAA games include franchises like \"Call of Duty,\" \"The Legend of Zelda,\" and \"Grand Theft Auto.\"",
